place.name: SOUTHWICK
place.gazetteerText: SOUTHWICK, a parish in Oundle district, Northampton; 2¾ miles NNW of Oundle r. station. Post town, Oundle. Acres, 1,320. Real property, £1,931-Pop., 130. Houses, 29. The property belongs to G. Capron, Esq. The living is a vicarage in the diocese of Peterborough. Value, £90.* Patron, G. Capron, Esq. The church is good. Charities, £24. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
